            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Mr. <addressee>Joseph M. Asch</addressee>
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>/ </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">When I came back to town last evening I understood that you should
                have/ said, that I had written a letter to <placeName>New York</placeName>
                cautioning the people there against/ giving any thing to the congr. of seceders of
                whom I have reason to believe that/ you are one. Now, as I have not seen you to
                speak with you for several weeks past,/ it is impossible for you to know any thing
                about my movements from your own/ knowledge, even if I had written such a letter,
                which permit me to say I would/ have been as much authorized to do, as for you to go
                on to <placeName>New York</placeName> to beg for/ a congr. which as yet exists only
                in imagination. But as I have written no letters to/ <placeName>N. Y</placeName><hi
                    rend="sup">o</hi>. except to Mr. <persName>Lyons</persName> the Haz. of the
                    <add>?</add> cong. in answer to a friendly one/ from him, and one to Mr.
                    <persName>Kursheedt</persName> on business relating to Mr.
                    <persName>Nelson</persName>, I demand/ of you the name of the person who
                invented the falsehood and told it to you. For my/ private letters I am not
                responsible to you, or any one, and I cannot permit/ my name to be used any longer
                to answer the purposes of the seceders. I would/ not have noticed the falsehood if
                it were the only one of its kind; but as I have/ been so often spoken of without
                cause I must insist upon your disclosing the/ name of your informant to the bearer
                of this, Mr. <persName>Sl. N. Carvalho</persName>./ <placeName>Phila</placeName><hi
                    rend="sup">a</hi>. Friday <date>July 10</date><hi rend="sup">th</hi>,
                    <date>Tamuz 9</date><hi rend="sup">th</hi>
                <date>5600</date></p>
            <p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">Isaac Leeser</persName>./ </p>
        </body>
